      "content": "wait, if you're just ignoring errors with a try-catch, aren't we just hiding actual bugs? if the data fetch fails on the dashboard, the test will still pass but the app is actually broken.\n\ncan you make sure the assertions are actually strong? i need to be sure that when the test passes, the user is definitely logged in and the data is actually showing up on the screen, not just that the page loaded. i can't have a \"green\" build if the dashboard is just a blank screen. can you refine the script to be really thorough with the checks?",
